		<description><![CDATA[The Inspiration
In April 2009 WIRED covered  a piece on digital art and it blew my mind.  The idea was to have graphic designers &#8230;]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>The Inspiration</strong></p>
<p>In April 2009 <a href="http://wired.com">WIRED</a> covered  a piece on digital art and it blew my mind.  The idea was to have graphic designers perform live in front of a live audience to one showcase their talents and two give the audience an idea of what goes into their work.  Given the opportunity I would definitely attend the next time around.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.cutandpaste.com/" target="_blank">Cut&amp;Paste</a> [Check them out]</p>
<div style="text-align: center;"><object id="flashObj" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="404" height="436" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="bgcolor" value="#FFFFFF" /><param name="flashVars" value="videoId=18978059001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fvideo%2Fcutpaste-competition-draws-designers%2F18978059001&amp;playerID=1813626064&amp;domain=embed&amp;" /><param name="base" value="http://admin.brightcove.com" /><param name="seamlesstabbing" value="false" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="swLiveConnect" value="true" /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9/1813626064?isVid=1&amp;publisherID=1564549380" /><param name="name" value="flashObj" /><param name="flashvars" value="videoId=18978059001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fvideo%2Fcutpaste-competition-draws-designers%2F18978059001&amp;playerID=1813626064&amp;domain=embed&amp;" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed id="flashObj" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="404" height="436" src="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9/1813626064?isVid=1&amp;publisherID=1564549380" name="flashObj" allowscriptaccess="always" swliveconnect="true" allowfullscreen="true" seamlesstabbing="false" base="http://admin.brightcove.com" flashvars="videoId=18978059001&amp;linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fvideo%2Fcutpaste-competition-draws-designers%2F18978059001&amp;playerID=1813626064&amp;domain=embed&amp;" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"></embed></object></div>
<div style="text-align: left;">Then, like the dude in the Win7 commercial, I was in the shower listening to some techno and thinking about that video&#8230;  it hit me like a ton of bricks.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>The Ultimate Concert [read Rave].<br />
</strong></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><strong><br />
</strong></div>
<div style="text-align: left;">So, let&#8217;s imagine a scenario where the likes of Dr. Dre, Daft Punk, Deadmaus, Timbaland, Will.I.Am, etc, got together and put together a monster concert/contest where DJs, Mixmasters, lyricists, and light techies battled it out, putting together what perhaps could become the greatest moment in music history.  A bunch of artists mixing and producing music they&#8217;re genuinely passionate about in real time, could be an epic moment.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>The Sponsors.</strong></div>
<div style="text-align: left;"><strong><br />
</strong>Let&#8217;s start with the money behind the scenes (because a party can only be as sweet as the money that powers and flows into it).</div>
<div style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://androwis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/bacardi.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-494" style="padding: 5 px;" title="bacardi" src="http://androwis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/bacardi.jpg" alt="bacardi, techno style" width="148" height="150" /></a><a href="http://androwis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/sdlkfwdlkfncwsldnvclksdnc.jpg"><img class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-379" title="Beats by Dre" src="http://androwis.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/sdlkfwdlkfncwsldnvclksdnc-150x150.jpg" alt="Beats by Dre" width="150" height="150" /></a> <strong>Bacardi:</strong> If the company is really as interested in contributing to the party seen as their commercials seem to suggest, what better event to sponsor than a massive music festival/dance/rave. Imagine the actors and the scenes in the commercials coming to life with some unique and crazy theme in each of the tour locations.   It would literally be the biggest and baddest party in town.</div>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<p><strong>Beats by Dre:</strong> The brother behind the scenes (aka&#8217;d the Doctor) is all about music and feeling every aspect of it. He has a niche market within the audiophile market but has transcended the music scenes with both his product line and his career as a producer. The synergy of his two passions could be phenomenal.  Being involved in the creation and presentation of the music might take his game to a new level.   Also, by sponsoring this type of event he would have the opportunity to carve out a new product line for concert halls, one that might end up blowing our minds (and clothes off).</p>
<p><strong>Red Bull (optional)</strong>: Energy is the theme. Wings are the claim. Game on.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>The Semantics</strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The idea of this establishment is to have a massive dance party to some freaking good music making contest.  Imagine a huge arena with four stations, the crowd in the middle and four teams of dj&#8217;s and light techies putting on a show.  Each team has access to all the same cutting edge technology and music (the contest being what they&#8217;re able to produce).  Each team has a set time limit with a 4 second overlapping transition between teams.  Everything they do is put on a projector above them so that the crowd can see the &#8220;behind the scenes&#8221;.  Depending on the popularity, all kinds of other music can be produced with different genres as an extension to this pseudo-underground scene.  [incorporating the likes of Daft Punk wouldn't hurt either].</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><br />
</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: left;">[photo by <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/night_star_pictures/3480019636/in/photostream/" target="_blank">NightStarPictures</a>]</div>
]]></content:encoded>
